    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 4 for MRL 2 Class II device. NIH prediction error of 7% at nominal operating point is within the 15% acceptance threshold. Pressure head validation confirms flow-field fidelity across all 5 COU operating points. The Giersiepen–Wurzinger model form is well-established in the literature and validated against FDA benchmark data. The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD model provides sufficient credibility to support the regulatory decision regarding worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the CPB device. Decision: Accepted.",
